	<strong>US State of California OEHHA Proposes to Repeal Outdated Requirements Related to Warning for BPA</strong>
	<p>On February 17, 2017, the California Office of Environmental Health Hazard Assessment (OEHHA) <a href="https://oehha.ca.gov/proposition-65/crnr/notice-proposed-rulemaking-title-27-proposed-repeal-sections-2560730-and-2560731" target="_blank">proposed to repeal outdated California Code of Regulations (CCR) section 25607.30 and 25607.31</a> related to warnings for exposure to Bisphenol A (BPA) from canned and bottled foods and beverages.</p>
