	<a href="javascript://" class="learnmore" style="float:left;">Read More</a>
	<div style="clear:both;"></div>
	<div class="moretext">
		<p>In this proposed action, no new provisions will be added and sections 25607.30 and 25607.31 will be removed due to the conflict with the regular rulemaking adopted previously (See <a href="http://www.asiainspection.com/regulatory-updates/January-2017/california-amendment-bottled-foods-beverages">previous story</a> in Regulatory Recap: January 2017). Therefore, upon approval, canned and bottled foods and beverages that cause exposures to BPA are deemed in compliance if the standard point-of-sale warning is provided according to <a href="https://govt.westlaw.com/calregs/Document/I2E352FE653364F099FD78F6185C79D00?viewType=FullText&originationContext=documenttoc&transitionType=CategoryPageItem&contextData=(sc.Default)" target="_blank">section 25603.3 (f) and (g) of CCR</a>.</p>
